 FLANGE GUSSET DESIGN
 
   For 1 bolt row, D1=Edge/2.0+(PltLen-d)/4.0                        =     111.0 mm
   D1<A so C=(1.0-D1/AA/2.0)*MaxBr*D1*B                              =    120.56 kN
   b=(pltlen-d)/2.0                                                  =     147.0 mm
   0<Gusset slope <1 so min gusset thickness=b/(Gusset Slope)/250*(Fy=       4.2 mm
   Selected gusset thickness, tg                                     =      10.0 mm
   h1 = (gusset slope)*b+(gusset height)                             =     197.0 mm
   Ang = ATAN(h1/b)                                                  =      0.93 mm
   Side gusset not used, so h2=h1-D1/2*TAN(Ang)                      =     122.6 mm
   ht=(h2^2+(b-d1/2)^2)^0.5                                          =     153.0 mm
   klr=0.75*ht/tg*3.464                                              =     39.75
   cc=(2*Pi^2*29000/Fy)^0.5                                          =    106.96
   klr < cc, therefore
   Allowable compression in gusset =
     Fyg*(1-(klr/cc)^2/2)/(5/3+3/8*klr/cc-(klr/cc)^3/8)              =       0.0 MN/m2
   Actual compression in gusset = C/tg/D1/sin(ang)^2                 =     169.0 MN/m2
   Allowable tension in gusset = 0.6*Fyg                             =     207.0 MN/m2
   TenAct=Ten*2*(1-Perf)                                             =     45.66 kN
   Actual tension in gusset = TenAct/tg/D1/SIN(Ang)^2                =      64.0 MN/m2
 
 WELDS TO FLANGE GUSSET
 
   Perf, percentage of force to flange = (G/2)^3/((G/2)^3+a^3)       =      0.18
   Actual shear in weld, flange gusset to base plate
     = 2*Ten/(PltLen-d) * (1-Perf)                                   =      0.16 kN/mm
   Calculations for flange gusset to flange weld
     F = Ten/h1 * (1-perf)                                           =      0.12 kN/mm
     D1<A so C=(1.0-D1/AA/2.0)*MaxBr*D1*B/2                          =     60.28 kN
     Actual shear in weld, flange gusset to flange
     = MAX(F,C/(2*h1))                                               =      0.15 kN/mm
 
 FLANGE WELD TO BASE PLATE
   Fo, space from flange to first outside row                        =      72.0 mm
   Beff, effective width = (FlgWid-G)/2+Fo                           =      97.0 mm
   Compression in bolts, so F2=Ten*2                                 =     59.19 kN
   Flange gusset used, so F=F2/2
   Splice type not FA, so F=F/2
   Splice type FI, so F=F+F2/4
   Actual shear in weld, =F/beff                                     =      0.31 kN/mm
 
 WEB WELD TO BASE PLATE
   With DM 194=3 or 4, Actual shear in weld = V/Webdep/2             =      0.04 kN/mm
 
 WEB WELD TO BASE PLATE AT BOLTS
   F1 = V/Webdep/2                                                   =      0.04 kN/mm
   fw = G/2 - WebThk/2                                               =      47.5 mm
   fo = space from outside of flange to first bolt                   =      72.0 mm
   F2 = Ten/2/(fo+fw)                                                =      0.04 kN/mm
    Actual shear in weld = SQRT(F1^2+F2^2)                           =      0.13 kN/mm
